urls.title: A bald eagle, U.S. national bird, seen wintering in Hokkaido marsh | The Asahi Shimbun: Breaking News, Japan News and Analysis

MassWildlife says last week a rare Steller’s sea eagle was spotted along the Taunton River in Massachusetts, thousands of miles away from its home in Asia. This sea eagle is one of the largest raptors in the world, weighing up to 20 pounds with a wingspan of up to 8 feet! https://t.co/2icYpLVC5h
